verses.verse: A Song <S%H7892><s%> of degrees <S%H4609><s%>. Unto thee lift I up <S%H5375><s%> mine eyes <S%H5869><s%>, O thou that dwellest <S%H3427><s%> in the heavens <S%H8064><s%>.

Behold, as the eyes <S%H5869><s%> of servants <S%H5650><s%> look unto the hand <S%H3027><s%> of their masters <S%H113><s%>, and as the eyes <S%H5869><s%> of a maiden <S%H8198><s%> unto the hand <S%H3027><s%> of her mistress <S%H1404><s%>; so our eyes <S%H5869><s%> wait upon the LORD <S%H3068><s%> our God <S%H430><s%>, until that he have mercy <S%H2603><s%> upon us.
Have mercy <S%H2603><s%> upon us, O LORD <S%H3068><s%>, have mercy <S%H2603><s%> upon us: for we are exceedingly <S%H7227><s%> filled <S%H7646><s%> with contempt <S%H937><s%>.

Our soul <S%H5315><s%> is exceedingly <S%H7227><s%> filled <S%H7646><s%> with the scorning <S%H3933><s%> of those that are at ease <S%H7600><s%>, and with the contempt <S%H937><s%> of the proud <S%H3238><s%> <S%H1343><s%> <S%H1349><s%>.
